(3838, 2, '2016-03-19 13:55:07', '2016-03-19 13:55:07', '[vc_row][vc_column width="1/2" offset="vc_col-lg-3 vc_col-md-3 vc_col-xs-12"][porto_content_box skin="primary" box_effect="featured-box-effect-1" show_icon="yes" icon="fa fa-user"][bsf-info-box icon="none" icon_size="40" icon_color="" title="LEARN" pos="top" title_font_color="#0088cc"]First we learn about you and your history by asking a few simple questions[/bsf-info-box][/porto_content_box][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2" offset="vc_col-lg-3 vc_col-md-3 vc_col-xs-12"][porto_content_box skin="secondary" box_effect="featured-box-effect-1" show_icon="yes" icon="fa fa-book"][bsf-info-box icon="none" icon_size="40" icon_color="" title="EXAMINE" pos="top" title_font_color="#e36159"]Next we will take a detailed look at your ears using our non-invasive tools[/bsf-info-box][/porto_content_box][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2" offset="vc_col-lg-3 vc_col-md-3 vc_col-xs-12"][porto_content_box skin="tertiary" box_effect="featured-box-effect-1" show_icon="yes" icon="fa fa-trophy"][bsf-info-box icon="none" icon_size="40" icon_color="" title="EVALUATE" pos="top" title_font_color="#2baab1"]Here we’ll perform a few short tests to target your exact needs[/bsf-info-box][/porto_content_box][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2" offset="vc_col-lg-3 vc_col-md-3 vc_col-xs-12"][porto_content_box skin="quaternary" box_effect="featured-box-effect-1" show_icon="yes" icon="fa fa-cogs"][bsf-info-box icon="none" icon_size="40" icon_color="" title="RECOMMEND" pos="top" title_font_color="#383f48"]Finally we’ll provide a recommendation that will be crafted to your exact situation and lifestyle[/bsf-info-box][/porto_content_box][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_custom_heading text="WHAT IS A HEARING EVALUATION ?" font_container="tag:h4|text_align:left|color:%23666666" google_fonts="font_family:Open%20Sans%3A300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C600%2C600italic%2C700%2C700italic%2C800%2C800italic|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal" el_class="upper"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em;">A Hearing Evaluation is the first step in diagnosing your individual needs. It enables us to determine both where you are performing well, and where we may need to focus our efforts for improvement.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em;">These tests are used to determine the extent, type, and details of your particular hearing loss and are performed by one of our licensed hearing care professionals. During these quick tests, we uncover the information needed to provide you the best solution possible.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_single_image image="4112" img_size="full" alignment="center" style="vc_box_shadow"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][bsf-info-box icon="Defaults-crosshairs" icon_size="28" icon_color="#662d6c" title="Air Conduction Testing" hover_effect="style_2" pos="top"][/bsf-info-box][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][bsf-info-box icon="Defaults-user-md" icon_size="28" icon_color="#662d6c" title="Bone Conduction Testing" hover_effect="style_2" pos="top"][/bsf-info-box][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][bsf-info-box icon="Defaults-bullhorn" icon_size="28" icon_color="#662d6c" title="Speech Testing" hover_effect="style_2" pos="top"][/bsf-info-box][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row bg_type="bg_color" bg_override="full" bg_color_value="#ffffff"][vc_column][vc_column_text][/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: left; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em;">The entire evaluation should last for between 20-40 minutes. Once the test is complete, we will spend some time talking about your results and make a recommendation for the next course of action.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="AFTER YOUR EVALUATION" font_container="tag:h4|text_align:left|color:%23666666" google_fonts="font_family:Open%20Sans%3A300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C600%2C600italic%2C700%2C700italic%2C800%2C800italic|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em;">After your evaluation is complete, we will spend some time discussing the results. We will carefully outline our findings and make recommendations as necessary. During this time don’t be afraid to ask questions. We want you to be comfortable and informed. After all, hearing care is a journey, not a quick fix.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="WHY DO I NEED A HEARING EVALUATION ?" font_container="tag:h4|text_align:left|color:%23666666" google_fonts="font_family:Open%20Sans%3A300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C600%2C600italic%2C700%2C700italic%2C800%2C800italic|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em;">A complete evaluation identifies hearing loss and gives us important information needed to provide help. Since there are different types of hearing loss , each needs to be treated in a specific way. This evaluation uncovers key information that tells us where and how to focus treatment.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em;">If it is determined that you could benefit from hearing devices, we offer a wide range of the latest technology and can recommend the right solution for your needs.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row bg_type="bg_color" bg_color_value="#ffffff" css=".vc_custom_1458831734705{padding-top: 15px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="CAN I BRING SOMEONE WITH ME ?" font_container="tag:h4|text_align:left|color:%23666666" google_fonts="font_family:Open%20Sans%3A300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C600%2C600italic%2C700%2C700italic%2C800%2C800italic|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em;">Yes! In fact, we encourage you to bring a family member or loved one to your evaluation. Since hearing loss effects more than just you, it’s beneficial to bring someone you trust to help digest the information and recommendations.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Hearing Evaluations', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hearing-evaluations', '', '', '2016-05-24 06:10:05', '2016-05-24 06:10:05', '', 0, 'http://www.riseforwar.com/?page_id=3838', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(3839, 2, '2016-03-19 13:55:29', '2016-03-19 13:55:29', '[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; text-align: justify;">Once you have completed a hearing evaluation and it is determined you would benefit from hearing devices, we will provide a recommendation on the right product for you. Upon selection, we will program your new hearing devices specifically to your needs. Since no two patients are the same, we will make sure that your hearing aids are programmed to meet your exact specifications. From there we will discuss the ins and outs including:</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/3"][porto_content_box skin="primary" box_style="featured-boxes-style-6" box_effect="featured-box-effect-6" show_icon="yes" icon="fa fa-check-square-o"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h4><span style="color: #666666;">How to Use Them</span></h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/porto_content_box][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][porto_content_box skin="primary" box_style="featured-boxes-style-6" box_effect="featured-box-effect-6" show_icon="yes" icon="fa fa-check-square-o"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h4><span style="color: #666666;">How to put them in correctly</span></h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/porto_content_box][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][porto_content_box skin="primary" box_style="featured-boxes-style-6" box_effect="featured-box-effect-6" show_icon="yes" icon="fa fa-check-square-o"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h4><span style="color: #666666;">How to remove them properly</span></h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/porto_content_box][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2" css=".vc_custom_1458898258663{padding-left: 170px !important;}"][porto_content_box skin="primary" box_style="featured-boxes-style-6" box_effect="featured-box-effect-6" show_icon="yes" icon="fa fa-check-square-o"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h4><span style="color: #666666;">How to change batteries</span></h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/porto_content_box][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2" css=".vc_custom_1458898282709{padding-right: 170px !important;}"][porto_content_box skin="primary" box_style="featured-boxes-style-6" box_effect="featured-box-effect-6" show_icon="yes" icon="fa fa-check-square-o"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h4><span style="color: #666666;">How to clean them</span></h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/porto_content_box][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; text-align: center;">We will make sure you are completely comfortable with using them and be here should you have any questions moving forward.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="WHAT CAN I EXPECT WHEN WEARING THEM ?" font_container="tag:h4|text_align:left|color:%23666666" google_fonts="font_family:Open%20Sans%3A300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C600%2C600italic%2C700%2C700italic%2C800%2C800italic|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em;">If it is your first time using hearing aids, it will feel a little different. That’s OK! It’s completely normal. It takes some time for your brain to adjust to hearing different sounds that it may have been missing.\r\nOur professionals will ask you a number of questions and perform some quick tests to ensure you are getting the most out of them. The sounds should be clear and comfortable. We will tweak them to make sure you are hearing as clearly as possible.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="WHAT IF I NEED AN ADJUSTMENT ?" font_container="tag:h4|text_align:left|color:%23666666" google_fonts="font_family:Open%20Sans%3A300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C600%2C600italic%2C700%2C700italic%2C800%2C800italic|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em;">Hearing care is a journey, not a quick fix. We are here for you every step of the way. We schedule routine follow-ups, but if you feel like you need some adjustments at any point just give us a call. We’ll get you taken care of right away.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Hearing Aid Fittings', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hearing-aid-fittings', '', '', '2016-03-26 12:15:50', '2016-03-26 12:15:50', '', 0, 'http://www.riseforwar.com/?page_id=3839', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(3840, 2, '2016-03-19 13:55:44', '2016-03-19 13:55:44', '[vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; text-align: justify;">Much like any electronic device, your hearing aids are made up of many small parts. They need to be maintained and occasionally serviced. If you should experience an issue that needs repair, bring them to us for a diagnosis. Generally, we can get them fixed using a number of tools and supplies that we have in the office.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; text-align: justify;">However, sometimes a repair requires more than we are capable of handling. In this instance, we may need to send your hearing aids back to the manufacturer. In this event, we will work with you to make this as painless of a process as possible. We will make sure to cover the details of your warranty and repair process clearly so you know exactly what to expect.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_empty_space height="50px"][vc_single_image image="3942" img_size="full" alignment="center"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Hearing Aid Repair', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hearing-aid-repair', '', '', '2016-04-12 07:11:35', '2016-04-12 07:11:35', '', 0, 'http://www.riseforwar.com/?page_id=3840', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(3841, 2, '2016-03-19 13:56:01', '2016-03-19 13:56:01', '[vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em;">One of the leading causes of hearing loss is prolonged exposure to noise. While this is generally irreversible, it is also avoidable by using hearing protection. If you are in a loud-noise environment, effective hearing protection is invaluable. While store-bought ear plugs do offer a small degree of protection, custom ear plugs offer maximum protection that is designed specifically for your ears. Depending on your work environment and noise exposure, we can make a recommendation on the specific type of ear plugs that would benefit you most. Since there are many types, we will want to uncover the right solution for your exact needs.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_single_image image="4113" img_size="full" alignment="center" style="vc_box_shadow_border"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Ear Plugs & Protection', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ear-plugs-protection', '', '', '2016-05-24 06:11:19', '2016-05-24 06:11:19', '', 0, 'http://www.riseforwar.com/?page_id=3841', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(3842, 2, '2016-03-19 13:58:17', '2016-03-19 13:58:17', '[vc_row][vc_column][vc_single_image image="3947" img_size="full" alignment="center"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: center; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em;">Hearing aids come in a wide range of technology levels and styles. They are offered in various levels ranging from ‘Entry-level’ to ‘Premium’. Within each level different technology and features are available. Some are designed for active lifestyles where others are for those in need of a ‘Power’ instrument. Choosing the right one depends on your specific needs and requirements. Our hearing care professionals are experts in each and can help you make the right choice.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_separator color="custom" gap="tall" gradient="yes"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="THINGS TO CONSIDER" font_container="tag:h4|text_align:center|color:%23666666" google_fonts="font_family:Open%20Sans%3A300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C600%2C600italic%2C700%2C700italic%2C800%2C800italic|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal" css=".vc_custom_1458907341780{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 10px !important;}"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/4"][porto_content_box skin="primary" box_style="featured-boxes-style-7" box_effect="featured-box-effect-7" show_icon="yes" icon="fa fa-volume-up"][vc_column_text]<strong style="text-transform: uppercase;">The degree of hearing loss</strong>[/vc_column_text][/porto_content_box][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][porto_content_box skin="primary" box_style="featured-boxes-style-7" box_effect="featured-box-effect-7" show_icon="yes" icon="fa fa-bullhorn"][vc_column_text]<strong style="text-transform: uppercase;">Dexterity</strong>[/vc_column_text][/porto_content_box][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][porto_content_box skin="primary" box_style="featured-boxes-style-7" box_effect="featured-box-effect-7" show_icon="yes" icon="fa fa-usd"][vc_column_text]<strong style="text-transform: uppercase;">Budget</strong>[/vc_column_text][/porto_content_box][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][porto_content_box skin="primary" box_style="featured-boxes-style-7" box_effect="featured-box-effect-7" show_icon="yes" icon="fa fa-tree"][vc_column_text]<strong style="text-transform: uppercase;">Lifestyle</strong>[/vc_column_text][/porto_content_box][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/3"][porto_content_box skin="primary" box_style="featured-boxes-style-7" box_effect="featured-box-effect-7" show_icon="yes" icon="fa fa-female"][vc_column_text]<strong style="text-transform: uppercase;">Cosmetics</strong>[/vc_column_text][/porto_content_box][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][porto_content_box skin="primary" box_style="featured-boxes-style-7" box_effect="featured-box-effect-7" show_icon="yes" icon="fa fa-leaf"][vc_column_text]<strong style="text-transform: uppercase;">Skin Sensitivities</strong>[/vc_column_text][/porto_content_box][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][porto_content_box skin="primary" box_style="featured-boxes-style-7" box_effect="featured-box-effect-7" show_icon="yes" icon="fa fa-medkit"][vc_column_text]<strong style="text-transform: uppercase;">Medical Considerations</strong>[/vc_column_text][/porto_content_box][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_separator color="custom" gap="tall" gradient="yes"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row bg_type="bg_color" bg_override="full" bg_color_value="#fff"][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="IN-THE-EAR (ITE)" font_container="tag:h4|text_align:center|color:%23666666" google_fonts="font_family:Open%20Sans%3A300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C600%2C600italic%2C700%2C700italic%2C800%2C800italic|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal" css=".vc_custom_1458907341780{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 10px !important;}"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1458832567604{margin-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<p style="text-align: center; font-size: 16px;">Hearing aids worn in the ear are generally custom-fit based on an impression of the ear. There are a variety of ITE styles that are available.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2" css=".vc_custom_1458809447966{padding-top: 30px !important;}"][vc_custom_heading text="INVISIBLE IN-THE-CANAL (IIC)" font_container="tag:h4|text_align:left|color:%23666666" google_fonts="font_family:Open%20Sans%3A300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C600%2C600italic%2C700%2C700italic%2C800%2C800italic|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal" css=".vc_custom_1458907397278{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 10px !important;}"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1458879927696{margin-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em;">IIC instruments are the smallest custom hearing aids available. They sit in the second bend of the canal and are nearly invisible to the naked eye. They are designed for mild to moderate hearing loss.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="3950" img_size="full" alignment="center" style="vc_box_shadow_border" css=".vc_custom_1458906855578{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="3951" img_size="medium" alignment="center" style="vc_box_shadow_border" css=".vc_custom_1458906880099{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2" css=".vc_custom_1458809476817{padding-top: 30px !important;}"][vc_custom_heading text="COMPLETE IN-THE-CANAL (CIC)" font_container="tag:h4|text_align:left|color:%23666666" google_fonts="font_family:Open%20Sans%3A300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C600%2C600italic%2C700%2C700italic%2C800%2C800italic|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal" css=".vc_custom_1458907477316{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 10px !important;}"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1458879951050{margin-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em;">CIC instruments fit deeply into the ear canal. Slightly larger than the IIC, they are still relatively hard to see. They are designed for mild to moderate hearing loss.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2" css=".vc_custom_1458809310608{padding-top: 50px !important;}"][vc_custom_heading text="IN-THE-CANAL (ITC) or HALF SHELL" font_container="tag:h4|text_align:left|color:%23666666" google_fonts="font_family:Open%20Sans%3A300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C600%2C600italic%2C700%2C700italic%2C800%2C800italic|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal" css=".vc_custom_1458907540110{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 10px !important;}"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1458879971900{margin-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em;">ITC instruments sit in the lower portion of the outer ear bowl. Since they are slightly larger than the CIC, they are able to hold additional features. These include a larger battery, directional microphones, and volume controls. They are designed for mild to moderate hearing loss.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="3952" img_size="medium" alignment="center" style="vc_box_shadow_border" css=".vc_custom_1458906896116{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="3953" img_size="medium" alignment="center" style="vc_box_shadow_border" css=".vc_custom_1458906912198{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2" css=".vc_custom_1458809332282{padding-top: 50px !important;}"][vc_custom_heading text="IN-THE-EAR (ITE) or FULL SHELL" font_container="tag:h4|text_align:left|color:%23666666" google_fonts="font_family:Open%20Sans%3A300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C600%2C600italic%2C700%2C700italic%2C800%2C800italic|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal" css=".vc_custom_1458912707519{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 10px !important;}"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1458880019937{margin-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em;">Full shell instruments fill the entire outer ear bowl. Due to their larger size, they allow for more features and functions. These include a larger battery, directional microphones, volume controls, and can fit larger receivers for more severe hearing losses. They are designed for mild to severe hearing losses.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_separator][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row bg_type="bg_color" bg_override="full" bg_color_value="#fff"][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="BEHIND-THE-EAR (BTE)" font_container="tag:h4|text_align:center|color:%23666666" google_fonts="font_family:Open%20Sans%3A300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C600%2C600italic%2C700%2C700italic%2C800%2C800italic|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal" css=".vc_custom_1458907621796{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 10px !important;}"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1458881111421{margin-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<p style="text-align: center; line-height: 1.8em; font-size: 16px;">Behind-the-Ear instruments sit behind or on top of the outer ear with a tube that connects to an ear tip or mold inside of the ear. BTE’s offer the widest range of features, colors, battery types, and degrees of power. Today, they’re offered in small, discreet designs that are often unnoticeable when worn. For those who prefer to “show them off”, they also come in multiple colors and designs.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2" css=".vc_custom_1458809447966{padding-top: 30px !important;}"][vc_custom_heading text="MINI BTE" font_container="tag:h4|text_align:left|color:%23666666" google_fonts="font_family:Open%20Sans%3A300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C600%2C600italic%2C700%2C700italic%2C800%2C800italic|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal" css=".vc_custom_1458907651486{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 10px !important;}"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1458880433638{margin-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em;">Mini BTE styles are designed to hide behind the outer ear and have ultra-thin tubing to discreetly route sound into the ear. The tubing typically connects to a soft tip that sits in the ear canal but doesn’t occlude it. The result is a natural, open feeling as airflow and sound enter the ear naturally around the tip, while amplified sound enters through the tip. This is known as “open fitting” and is recommended for mild to moderate hearing loss.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="3954" img_size="medium" alignment="center" style="vc_box_shadow_border" css=".vc_custom_1458906930997{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="3955" img_size="medium" alignment="center" style="vc_box_shadow_border" css=".vc_custom_1458906949138{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2" css=".vc_custom_1458809476817{padding-top: 30px !important;}"][vc_custom_heading text="RECEIVER-IN-THE-EAR (RITE) or RECEIVER-IN-CANAL (RIC)" font_container="tag:h4|text_align:left|color:%23666666" google_fonts="font_family:Open%20Sans%3A300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C600%2C600italic%2C700%2C700italic%2C800%2C800italic|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal" css=".vc_custom_1458907706718{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 10px !important;}"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1458880731440{margin-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em;">RITE hearing aid styles are BTEs that have the speaker built into the ear tip instead of the main body of the hearing aid. It is slightly larger than the Mini BTE but is still relatively unnoticeable when worn. They are designed for mild to severe hearing loss.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2" css=".vc_custom_1458809310608{padding-top: 50px !important;}"][vc_custom_heading text="BEHIND-THE-EAR (BTE) WITH EARMOLD" font_container="tag:h4|text_align:left|color:%23666666" google_fonts="font_family:Open%20Sans%3A300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C600%2C600italic%2C700%2C700italic%2C800%2C800italic|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal" css=".vc_custom_1458907771091{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 10px !important;}"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1458880797876{margin-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em;">BTEs with earmolds have a longer shape that follows the contour behind the outer ear. Their larger size enables them to house features such as a program button and volume control. The earmold color and style, as well as the wearer’s hairstyle, determine exactly how they’ll look on each person. They are designed for mild to profound hearing loss.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="3956" img_size="medium" alignment="center" style="vc_box_shadow_border" css=".vc_custom_1458906964951{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Hearing Aid Styles', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hearing-aid-styles', '', '', '2016-05-20 13:11:40', '2016-05-20 13:11:40', '', 0, 'http://www.riseforwar.com/?page_id=3842', 0, 'page', '', 0),
