(4050, 2, '2016-05-18 13:04:18', '2016-05-18 13:04:18', '[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1460434945375{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;}"]\r\n<p style="font-size: 16px; text-align: left;">At Sage we work with most major insurance companies including:</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="3997" img_size="full" alignment="center"][vc_single_image image="3995" img_size="full" alignment="center"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="3998" img_size="full" alignment="center"][vc_single_image image="3996" img_size="full" alignment="center"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">If you don’t see your insurance listed, give us a call. We’re happy to discuss your options.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em;">CareCredit is the most widely used patient finance program. CareCredit works like a credit card but is exclusive for healthcare services. They offer monthly payment options, no up-front costs to patients, no prepayment penalties and no annual fees. Short-term, no-interest plans are available as well as longer term plans with fixed interest rates. Speak with our team of professionals to see if this may be an option for you.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_empty_space][vc_single_image image="3895" img_size="medium" alignment="center"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Insurance and Financing', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '3857-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-05-18 13:04:18', '2016-05-18 13:04:18', '', 3857, 'http://www.riseforwar.com/3857-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4052, 2, '2016-04-12 04:46:01', '2016-04-12 04:46:01', '[vc_row][vc_column width="1/2" offset="vc_col-lg-4 vc_col-md-4 vc_col-xs-12"][porto_content_box skin="secondary" box_effect="featured-box-effect-1" show_icon="yes"][bsf-info-box icon_type="custom" img_width="120" title="\n\n<center>Outer Ear</center>" pos="top" title_font_color="#e36159"]\n<div class="xxxb_text_column xxxb_content_element vc_custom_1458819767714">\n<div class="xxxb_wrapper">\n\nThe Pinna is the visible portion of the outer ear. It collects sound waves and channels them into the ear canal where the sound is amplified. The sound waves then travel toward a flexible, oval membrane at the end of the ear canal called the eardrum. The eardrum then begins to vibrate.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n[/bsf-info-box][/porto_content_box][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2" offset="vc_col-lg-4 vc_col-md-4 vc_col-xs-12"][porto_content_box skin="quaternary" box_effect="featured-box-effect-1" show_icon="yes"][bsf-info-box icon_type="custom" img_width="120" title="\n\n<center>Middle Ear</center>" pos="top" title_font_color="#383f48"]\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The vibrations from the eardrum set the ossicles into motion. The ossicles are three tiny bones (smallest in the human body): Malleus (hammer), Incus (anvil) and Stapes (stirrup) which further amplify the sound.\nThe stapes attaches to the oval window that connects the middle ear to the inner ear. The Eustachian tube, which opens into the middle ear, is responsible for equalizing the pressure between the air outside the ear to that within the middle ear.</p>\n[/bsf-info-box][/porto_content_box][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2" offset="vc_col-lg-4 vc_col-md-4 vc_col-xs-12"][porto_content_box skin="secondary" box_effect="featured-box-effect-1" show_icon="yes"][bsf-info-box icon_type="custom" img_width="120" title="\n\n<center>Inner Ear</center>" pos="top" title_font_color="#e36159"]\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The sound waves enter the inner ear and then into a snail shaped organ called the cochlea. The cochlea is filled with a fluid that moves in response to the vibrations from the oval window. As the fluid moves, thousands of nerve endings are then set into motion. These nerve endings transform the vibrations into electrical impulses that then travel along the auditory nerve to the brain.\nThe brain then interprets these signals and this is how we hear. The inner ear also contains the vestibular organ that is responsible for balance.</p>\n[/bsf-info-box][/porto_content_box][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_single_image image="3941" img_size="full" alignment="center"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'How the Ear Works', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '3832-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-04-12 04:46:01', '2016-04-12 04:46:01', '', 3832, 'http://www.riseforwar.com/3832-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4053, 2, '2016-04-12 05:03:42', '2016-04-12 05:03:42', '[vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]\n<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; text-align: justify;">Much like any electronic device, your hearing aids are made up of many small parts. They need to be maintained and occasionally serviced. If you should experience an issue that needs repair, bring them to us for a diagnosis. Generally, we can get them fixed using a number of tools and supplies that we have in the office.</p>\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]\n<p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; text-align: justify;">However, sometimes a repair requires more than we are capable of handling. In this instance, we may need to send your hearing aids back to the manufacturer. In this event, we will work with you to make this as painless of a process as possible. We will make sure to cover the details of your warranty and repair process clearly so you know exactly what to expect.</p>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_single_image image="3942" img_size="large" alignment="center"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Hearing Aid Repair', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '3840-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-04-12 05:03:42', '2016-04-12 05:03:42', '', 3840, 'http://www.riseforwar.com/3840-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4055, 2, '2016-05-18 10:47:32', '2016-05-18 10:47:32', '[vc_row][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width="2/3"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">David King is a Hearing Care Specialist that has served patients in Oregon and Arizona for over 13 years.  He currently lives in Beaverton with his wife, Jaimie, and their two young children, Parker and Haley.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The cornerstone of David''s professionalism is built on his commitment to serving the hearing impaired and to exceed the expectations of his patients.  After working for over a decade with a National Audiology Company, he and his wife decided to open their own practice to better serve the needs of their community.  By combining integrity and knowledge he naturally demonstrates a unique ability to educate his patients and their families about the strategies and care of hearing impairment.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">While using state of the art equipment and technology, David provides an array of screenings, hearing tests, aural rehabilitation and expansive knowledge of both conventional and digital instruments.  With over a decade of experience in the hearing health care field, David''s commitment to excellent patient care is evident in each and every person he works with.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">David understands the importance of taking the time to really listen to his patients.  He creates an environment where open and honest communication can take place and his patients can make decisions about their hearing needs based on facts and years of success, all without the feeling of being rushed or pressured.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">David''s knowledge in communication disorders has helped improve the quality of life for thousands of people in his community.  By starting Sage Hearing Solutions, he now has the ability to offer the same quality service at more affordable prices to those in need of Hearing Health Care.  You can depend on David to provide the absolute best solution for you.  We are confident that you will be satisfied with his skills and desire to not only meet your expectations, but also far exceed them.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][vc_empty_space height="80px"][vc_single_image image="3959" img_size="full" alignment="center" style="vc_box_outline_circle_2"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Our Professionals', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '3826-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-05-18 10:47:32', '2016-05-18 10:47:32', '', 3826, 'http://www.riseforwar.com/3826-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
